00:55:08.754 --> 00:55:12.534
CD69. So even at these low doses, these cells are looking

954
00:55:12.634 --> 00:55:16.466
good.This is looking at the second

955
00:55:16.486 --> 00:55:20.366
patient. This is the patient who actually, by contrast,

956
00:55:20.646 --> 00:55:22.926
the tumor actually progressed by day 56.

957
00:55:23.366 --> 00:55:27.186
And now when we look at the tumor at the T cells, you can see the four cells

958
00:55:27.226 --> 00:55:30.986
are actually all exhausted and that's true for the CD8

959
00:55:31.026 --> 00:55:31.846
cells as well.

960
00:55:32.766 --> 00:55:36.246
And so we obviously need to do more, and one of them is obviously to put in these

961
00:55:36.326 --> 00:55:36.986
IFPs

962
00:55:37.906 --> 00:55:41.846
or provide co-stimulation in some way to enhance their persistence.

